Anonymous Fri 08 Dec 2023 15:39:58 No.61686569 Report
Quoted By:
>>61686276
>Are they ashamed of being outclassed?
Ashamed is not the right word. Most drawfrens accept that AI will draw/paint better than they can. If not already, then at some point in their lifetimes. Most people can't even tell the difference between a good gen with minimal in painting, and good art anymore. Artists accept that they are outclassed.

The flautist/recorders example doesn't work because the flautist doesn't have to live with the recorder players. In the case of an image board, AI and hand-drawn art occupy the same space, but AI can be produced more cheaply and quickly. Each thread has a limited life span of 300 images. If each thread contained 100 ai posts and only 2 or 3 new drawings, then the thread artists wouldn't get nearly as much attention. They'd get drowned out. Some would be inclined to move to sites or generals that prohibit AI art.

Threads would also die much faster if many people decided to post their AI gens. But too much of anything is spam, no matter what it is.
